{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos508.HadwigerNelsonProblem https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos508.HadwigerNelsonProblem.","id":"vf_2f231b510c4a2232","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #508: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. What is the chromatic number of the plane? That is, what is the smallest number of colours required to colour $\\mathbb{R}^2$ such that no two points of the same colour are distance $1$ apart? Current best: An equilateral triangle trivially shows that $\\chi\\geq 3$. There are several small graphs that show $\\chi\\geq 4$ (in particular the Moser spindle and Golomb graph). The best bounds currently known are\\[5 \\leq \\chi \\leq 7.\\]The lower bound is due to de Grey \\cite{dG18}. The upper bound can be seen by colouring the plane by tesselating by hexagons with diameter slightly less than $1$. Prize: no. Tags: geometry, ramsey theory.","id":"vf_b0bc9414824e9d55","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/508.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_2f231b510c4a2232","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:508","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_2f231b510c4a2232","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_b0bc9414824e9d55","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_b0bc9414824e9d55","source_root":"sha256:540d49